<h2>Making more money using Kindle Direct Publishing?</h2>
<p>Book sales is the most obvious way to make money from self publishing. You will either earn royalties (from self publishing platforms such as amazon's kindle direct publishing/kdp) or revenues (if you print, distribute and sell your book yourself). In terms of royalties, authors can earn as much as 35 percent for print books up to around 70 percent for ebooks (as of this writing), depending on the platform used. Those are decent returns for almost any business venture!.</p>
<h3>Has anyone ever used Kindle Direct Publishing (KDP) to self-publish your work? W</h3>
<p>It&amp;rsquo;s not possible to write a list like this without kindle direct publishing&amp;mdash;which is widely respected as one of the foremost self-publishing platforms currently available. Working under the amazon family of products, there&amp;rsquo;s nothing these guys can&amp;rsquo;t help you with on your next self-publishing project. And, unlike other e-publishers, you can update your book online &amp;mdash; even after it&amp;rsquo;s been published.</p>
<p>If you self publish your print books as print on demand on kindle direct publishing (kdp), there is no way to offer a signed copy to your reader buyers. The only way you can offer signed copies for sale on amazon is by becoming an amazon seller through the fulfillment by amazon fba program. That has a host of costs and requirements that might not make it worth doing because of the limited number of signed copies you&amp;rsquo;d actually sell.</p>
<p>Your craft book or ebook should not look self-published and should be as professionally and artfully presented as the projects you're featuring! for the best rendering of photos of techniques and completed projects at a reasonable cost for printed books, using a self-publishing platform with print on demand (pod) is recommended. You'll get commercial-level print quality without having to purchase boxes and boxes of books, as you would with standard commercial printing companies. With some platforms, such as amazon's kindle direct publishing (kdp, which encompasses the former createspace), you can purchase even just one book at a time. Plus, your readers can order from amazon direct without you ever having to personally ship a book!.</p>
<p>The most cost-effective and efficient way to do amazon self-publishing is through ebooks , which allows people to download your work directly to their devices, like the kindle ebook reader. And amazon has facilitated this process with kindle direct publishing program , which has no fees to use &amp;mdash; it&amp;rsquo;s self-publishing with no upfront costs. (you do need an amazon account. ).</p>
<h2>3 Things you can do to double your book sales.</h2>
<p>There are really only two things you can do to cost-effectively promote future book sales: build your fan base; and, market to that fan base. But your fan base isn&amp;rsquo;t a &amp;ldquo;set it and forget it&amp;rdquo; investment. Beyond the book launch, your fan base will take nurturing from now until you officially want to stop selling your books. That means investing in social media, podcasts, videos, blogs, events, email subscriber list building, and other public relations efforts to keep you top of mind for fans, both old and new.</p>
<p>Whether you have an official celebration or not, your book launch day is really your first day on the job of being a self published author. Yes, the job. You may write more books over time. But the writing isn&amp;rsquo;t the main focus anymore. You are now in the author and publisher business. You&amp;rsquo;ll be spending your days looking for ways to get your books and content into the hands, hearts, and minds of readers. That means time on social media channels recruiting new fans and engaging with existing ones. You&amp;rsquo;ll be creating fresh non-book content such as videos, podcasts, blogs, and social media posts to share with your fans.</p>
